            <tr>
              <td height="100%" align="left" valign="top" background="images/hkix_logo_04.jpg" style="background-repeat:no-repeat "><table width=800 border=0 cellpadding="5" cellspacing=0 bgcolor="#333333">
                <tr>
                  <td height="24" colspan="2" valign="top" bgcolor="#666666" class="title"><!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="header" -->&nbsp;Route Policy<!-- InstanceEndEditable --></td>
                </tr>
                <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="content" -->
                <tr bordercolor="#666666">
                  <td colspan="2" valign="top" background="images/hkix_bg_policies.jpg" style="background-repeat:no-repeat" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" class="normaltext"><table width="97%"  border="0" align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
                    <tr>
                      <td><p class="normaltext">The BGP Announcement Policy of Hong Kong Internet eXchange (HKIX) is as follows,</p>
                        <H3 class="header">1. Filtering</H3>
                        <H3 class="subhead2"><B>a. IP address filtering</B></H3>
                        <ul>
                          <LI>Applicable to general HKIX members. 
                          <LI>Filtering by IP addresses. 
                          <LI>Update via <A 
href="http://www.hkix.net/hkix/filter/filterupdate.html">Filter Update Agent</A> for each announcement.</LI>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="subhead2"><B>b. AS number filtering</B> </p>
                        <ul>
                          <LI>Applicable to HKIX members who have more than 5 Autonomous Systems (AS) connected and each AS contains at least one /20 or shorter prefix announced to the HKIX. 
                          <LI>Filtering by AS number orignated from the IAP's customer network. 
                          <LI>Update via <A 
href="http://www.hkix.net/hkix/filter/filterupdate.html">Filter Update Agent</A> for each announcement. 
                          <LI>Separate application is required, please make your application by e-mail to <A href="mailto:hkix-noc@cuhk.edu.hk">hkix-noc@cuhk.edu.hk</A>. </LI>
                        </ul>
                        <p>HKIX members should check the integrity of the filters and submit only the IP address or AS number that require for update. HKIX may reject the applications if the IP addresses or AS numbers had already included in the filter. </p>
                        <p>The minimum IP block accepted by the HKIX route server is /24.</p>
                        <H3 class="header">2. Non-filtering</H3>
                        <p class="subhead2"><B>Closer Peering Arrangement (CPA) Scheme</B> </p>
                        <ul>
                          <li>Applicable to HKIX members who are using AS filtering and advertising more than 2500 prefixes for 200+ different ASes to the HKIX. </li>
                          <li>All routes will be accepted by the route servers. </li>
                          <li>No need to submit filter update. </li>
                          <li>Separate application is required, please read <A 
href="cpa.htm">here</A> for details. </li>
                          </ul>
                        <p class="header">3. IPv6 BGP  Filtering </p>
                        <p><a href="file:///U|/DCNS/HKIX/DOC/webupdate/HKIX Web/route-server.htm"></a> HKIX have implemented   bogon filter for IPv6 address filtering. In   order to facilitate better routing management for IPv6 routes being advertised via HKIX/AS4635 MLPA Route Server, we highly recommend all participants to make use of BGP community tagging when they announce/receive IPv6 routes to/from the HKIX MLPA route server.</p>
                        <p><strong><span lang="EN-US">The BGP  communities  supported by HKIX MLPA route server</span></strong> <strong>(for  IPv6  only)</strong></p>
                        <table width="577" border="1">
                          <tr>
                            <th width="63" height="66" scope="row">1</th>
                            <td width="116"><div align="center"><span lang="EN-US"><strong>4635:900</strong></span></div></td>
                            <td width="376"><p><span lang="EN-US">Upstream / peer  routes announced by free IPv6 transit providers for use by those HKIX  participants which seek for free IPv6 transit over HKIX MLPA</span></p></td>
                          </tr>
                          <tr>
                            <th height="54" scope="row">2</th>
                            <td><div align="center"><span lang="EN-US"><strong>4635:800</strong></span></div></td>
                            <td><span lang="EN-US">Downstream / internal  routes seeking for peering only over HKIX MLPA but not for transit</span></td>
                          </tr>
                          <tr>
                            <th height="46" scope="row">3</th>
                            <td><div align="center"><span lang="EN-US"><strong>4635:700</strong></span></div></td>
                            <td><span lang="EN-US">Downstream / internal  routes seeking for transit over HKIX MLPA</span></td>
                          </tr>
                        </table>
                        <p class="link">&nbsp;</p>
                        <p class="style7"><span lang="EN-US">HKIX participants should tag  the routes  they announce to HKIX MLPA route server as follows:</span></p>
                        <p><span lang="EN-US"><strong>1</strong>. For HKIX  participants which  want to provide free IPv6 transit to other HKIX participants over HKIX  MLPA:</span></p>
                        <ul>
                          <li><span lang="EN-US">They  should announce  their upstream / peer routes with tag <strong>4635:900</strong></span></li>
                          <li><span lang="EN-US">They  should announce  their downstream / internal routes with tag <strong>4635:800</strong>.</span></li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><span lang="EN-US"><strong>2</strong>. For HKIX  participants which  want to do multilateral peering over HKIX only:</span></p>
                        <ul>
                          <li><span lang="EN-US"> They  should announce  their downstream / internal routes with tag <strong>4635:800</strong></span></li>
                          <li><span lang="EN-US">They  should NOT  announce their upstream / peer routes.</span></li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><span lang="EN-US"><strong>3</strong>. For HKIX  participants which  seek for transit over HKIX MLPA:</span></p>
                        <ul>
                          <li><span lang="EN-US"> They  should announce  their downstream / internal routes with tag <strong>4635:700</strong></span></li>
                          <li><span lang="EN-US"> They  should NOT  announce their upstream / peer routes.</span></li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="style7">&nbsp;</p>
                        <p class="style7"><span lang="EN-US">HKIX participants should process the routes  learned from HKIX MLPA route server as follows:</span></p>
                        <p><span lang="EN-US"><strong> 1</strong>. For HKIX  participants which  want to provide transit to other HKIX participants over HKIX MLPA:</span></p>
                        <ul>
                          <li><span lang="EN-US"> When  they see routes  with tag <strong>4635:900</strong>, they should just ignore them</span></li>
                          <li><span lang="EN-US">When  they see routes  with tag <strong>4635:800</strong>, they should re-distribute the routes to their  downstream /  internal networks only, but not to their upstream / peer networks</span></li>
                          <li><span lang="EN-US">When  they see routes  with tag <strong>4635:700</strong>, they should re-distribute the routes to all their  downstream  / internal / upstream / peer networks.</span></li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><span lang="EN-US"><strong>2</strong>. For HKIX  participants which  want to do multilateral peering over HKIX only:</span></p>
                        <ul>
                          <li><span lang="EN-US">When  they see routes  with tag <strong>4635:900</strong>, they should just ignore them</span></li>
                          <li><span lang="EN-US">When  they see routes  with tag <strong>4635:800</strong> and <strong>4635:700</strong>, they should re-distribute the routes to  their  downstream / internal networks only, but not to their upstream / peer  networks.</span></li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><span lang="EN-US"><strong>3</strong>. For HKIX  participants which  seek for transit over HKIX MLPA:</span></p>
                        <ul>
                          <li><span lang="EN-US"> They  should  re-distribute all the routes that they learn from HKIX MLPA route  server to  their downstream / internal networks only, but not to their upstream /  peer  networks.</span></li>
                        </ul>                        <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
                    </tr>
                  </table>                  <p class="normaltext">&nbsp;</p>
                  <p>&nbsp;</p>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
